    "body": "### Description\n\nI stumbled upon a pretty niche situation today where I'm trying to use `ccls` in a project without git (recently started to use jj instead). After some debugging it looks like ccls is not starting because there's no file/folder matching `root_markers` in my project. I tried to override it with:\n```lua\nlspconfig.ccls.setup({\n   root_markers = { \"flake.nix\", \".git\", \".jj\" },\n   capabilities = capabilities,\n   on_attach = on_attach,\n})\n\n```\nthis code. but to no avail.\n\nAlso on the same note can `.jj` be added to `root_markers` along side `.git` by default?",
