            "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
            "body": "> I stumbled upon a pretty niche situation today where I'm trying to use `ccls` in a project without git (recently started to use jj instead). After some debugging it looks like ccls is not starting because there's no file/folder matching `root_markers` in my project. I tried to override it with:\n> ```lua\n> lspconfig.ccls.setup({\n>    root_markers = { \"flake.nix\", \".git\", \".jj\" },\n>    capabilities = capabilities,\n>    on_attach = on_attach,\n> })\n> ```\n> this code. but to no avail.\n\n`lspconfig.ccls.setup()` is deprecated and doesn't even support `root_markers`. You want to use `vim.lsp.config`, e.g:\n\n```lua\n-- lua/ccls.lua\nreturn {\n  root_markers = { \"flake.nix\", \".git\", \".jj\" },\n}\n```\n\n> Also on the same note can `.jj` be added to `root_markers` along side `.git` by default?\n\n`.git` as a default root marker is actually going away:\n\n- https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/issues/3728",
